questions.solution:
Let $	heta =  rac{540^	ext{o}}{7}$, so $ rac{	heta}{2} =  rac{270^	ext{o}}{7} 
ot acksim 38.57^	ext{o}$, $ rac{	heta}{3} 
ot acksim 25.71^	ext{o}$, $ rac{2	heta}{3} 
ot acksim 51.43^	ext{o}$. Note that $ rac{	heta}{2} +  rac{	heta}{3} +  rac{2	heta}{3} = 2	heta =  rac{1080^	ext{o}}{7} 
ot acksim 154.29^	ext{o} < 180^	ext{o}$, all angles acute.

Consider the general identity for $	an x 	an(60^	ext{o} - x) 	an(60^	ext{o} + x) = 	an 3x$. Here $ rac{	heta}{2},  rac{	heta}{3},  rac{2	heta}{3}$ are not of that form directly, but relate to 7th roots.

Instead, use the reflection formula for the product $P = 	an rac{	heta}{3} 	an rac{2	heta}{3} 	an rac{	heta}{2}$. Note $	heta =  rac{540^	ext{o}}{7}$, so $3	heta/7 = 231.43^	ext{o} > 180^	ext{o}$, but work with known 7-gon identities.

**Key Insight**: For $	heta = 3  rac{180^	ext{o}}{7}$, the angles $ rac{	heta}{3} =  rac{180^	ext{o}}{7}$, $ rac{2	heta}{3} =  rac{360^	ext{o}}{7}$, $ rac{	heta}{2} =  rac{270^	ext{o}}{7}$ are permutations of $ rac{k 	imes 180^	ext{o}}{7}$ for $k=1,2,3$ (since $ rac{360^	ext{o}}{7} =  rac{180^	ext{o}}{7} 	imes 2$, etc.).

Thus $P = 	an rac{180^	ext{o}}{7} 	an rac{2 	imes 180^	ext{o}}{7} 	an rac{3 	imes 180^	ext{o}}{7} = 	an rac{\pi}{7} 	an rac{2\pi}{7} 	an rac{3\pi}{7}$ (in radians equivalent).

From the seed problem and standard result, this product equals $\sqrt{7}$.

**Verification via triple product identity**: Consider $	an(3x) =  rac{3	an x - 	an^3 x}{1 - 3	an^2 x}$, but for product over roots, use $\sin7x=0$ polynomial. The roots of the tangent product for heptagon give $P = 	an rac{\pi}{7}	an rac{2\pi}{7}	an rac{3\pi}{7} = \sqrt{7}$ (established result from complex roots or Vieta on $\tan7x$).

